parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to accidents, fires, or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Fuel odor
fuel leaks
fuel spraying from the fuel pump
fuel running down the hot exhaust pipe
sudden loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body cam can cause complete power loss to the engine, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Sudden loss of power
engine stalling
throttle body cam broken or cracked.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel strip can cause inaccurate fuel level readings, leading to unexpected fuel depletion, engine stalling, and accidents.
symptoms: Erratic fuel gauge readings
sudden drop in fuel level
fuel gauge displaying "---" miles to empty
inaccurate fuel level readings.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Bearing Failure Leading to Final Drive Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear bearing can cause the final drive to fail, leading to a loss of rear brakes, loss of power, and vibration, which can result in accidents or leave the rider stranded.
symptoms: Grinding noise from the rear of the bike
clicking noise from the rear of the bike
rear wheel play
final drive fluid leak
loss of rear brakes
vibration
and loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle cable assembly can cause the engine to idle, making it difficult or impossible to maintain speed or accelerate, which can lead to accidents or put the rider in harm's way.
symptoms: Clicking noise from the throttle body
engine idling
inability to maintain speed or accelerate.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unintended Acceleration and Loss of Engine Control
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of engine control and unintended acceleration can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The motorcycle accelerates without input from the rider
the throttle response is unresponsive or erratic
the engine RPM increases without warning
the motorcycle fails to slow down or respond to braking input.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Throttle Cable or Electronic Throttle System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle cable or electronic throttle system can cause the motorcycle to lose motive power or accelerate unintentionally, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The throttle feels unresponsive or stuck
the engine RPM increases or decreases without warning
the motorcycle fails to accelerate or decelerate as expected.
